{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":null,"await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"BigInt generator with boundary values (0, 1, -1, MAX_SAFE+1, large numbers) added. BigDecimal generator added. TS analyzer maps bigint primitive to complex:big_int. Go analyzer recognizes *big.Int, *big.Rat, *big.Float. Both frontends reconstruct BigInt values.","closed_at":"2026-02-27T05:39:32Z","closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"45c77a481f5881cc0ff310683999508bdaceb2424407ad44789dc605ee8ed6fa","created_at":"2026-02-27T04:47:15Z","created_by":"Ketan Gangatirkar","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"Full support for arbitrary-precision numeric types: generator, analyzer recognition, reconstruction, and tests.\n\n## What\n1. Core generators (input_gen.rs):\n   - generate_bigint: 0, 1, -1, MAX_SAFE_INTEGER+1 (9007199254740992), MIN_SAFE_INTEGER-1, very large (50+ digits), powers of 2\n   - generate_bigdecimal: 0, 0.01, -0.01, 0.1, 0.001, very precise (20+ decimal places), financial amounts\n   - Wire format: {\"__complex_type\": \"big_int\", \"value\": \"99999999999999999\"}, {\"__complex_type\": \"big_decimal\", \"value\": \"0.00000000000000001\"}\n   - String representation to avoid JSON number precision loss\n\n2. TS analyzer: Recognize bigint primitive type (ts.TypeFlags.BigInt)\n3. TS reconstruction: BigInt(value_string)\n4. Go analyzer: Recognize *big.Int, *big.Float (as BigDecimal), *big.Rat\n5. Go reconstruction: new(big.Int).SetString(value, 10), new(big.Float).SetString(value)\n\n## Solver\nTier 1 for BigInt (if fits i64) — comparisons reduce to Z3 Int. Falls back to fuzzing for values exceeding i64 range.\nTier 3 for BigDecimal — fuzzing with good boundaries is sufficient.\n\n## Export\n- Jest: BigInt('digits')\n- Go: new(big.Int).SetString(\"digits\", 10)\n\n## Integration test\nsafeDivide(a: bigint, b: bigint): bigint — division with zero-check branch\n\n##