{"acceptance_criteria":"","actor":"","agent_state":"","assignee":null,"await_id":"","await_type":"","close_reason":"Closed","closed_at":"2026-02-26T21:37:50Z","closed_by_session":"","compacted_at":null,"compacted_at_commit":null,"compaction_level":0,"content_hash":"31f092f176a63ef20ff443b06c6bcfdcaf54fedaa3e81e8a7ea49215e4d02e1b","created_at":"2026-02-25T05:02:27Z","created_by":"Ketan Gangatirkar","crystallizes":0,"defer_until":null,"description":"The z3-sys crate uses bindgen to generate Rust FFI bindings for Z3, which requires libclang at build time. This caused the devcontainer build to fail with 'Unable to find libclang'.\n\n## What was done (commit ddc41c8)\n\n### Devcontainer fix\n- Added `libclang-dev` to `.devcontainer/Dockerfile` apt packages. This provides both `libclang.so` and clang's resource directory (builtin headers like `stdbool.h`) inside the container.\n\n### Local dev fallback\n- Added `.cargo/config.toml` with `BINDGEN_EXTRA_CLANG_ARGS` set to `-I/usr/lib/gcc/x86_64-linux-gnu/13/include` (with `force = false`). This tells bindgen to use GCC's builtin headers when only `libclang1-18` (runtime .so) is installed without the full `libclang-dev` package. The `force = false` means it's a no-op when `libclang-dev` is installed or the env var is already set.\n\n### Go version fix\n- Fixed Go version from 1.25.7 (never released — Go went 1.24 → 1.26) to 1.24.4 in both `.devcontainer/Dockerfile` and `shatter-go/go.mod`.\n\n### Documentation\n- Added Prerequisites section to `CLAUDE.md` documenting the `libclang` requirement and how to install it.\n\n## Remaining concern\n- The GCC include path in `.cargo/config.toml` is hardcoded to GCC 13 on x86_64. Developers with a different GCC version need to update it manually (`gcc -print-file-name=include` to find the right path).","design":"","due_at":null,"ephemeral":0,"estimated_minutes":null,"event_kind":"","external_ref":null,"hook_bead":"","id":"str-13h","is_template":0,"issue_type":"task","last_activity":null,"metadata":"{}","mol_type":"","notes":"","original_size":null,"owner":"33678+ketang@users.noreply.github.com","payload":"","pinned":0,"priority":2,"quality_score":null,"rig":"","role_bead":"","role_type":"","sender":"","source_repo":"","source_system":"","spec_id":"","status":"closed","target":"","timeout_ns":0,"title":"fix the clang hacks needed to support z3-sys","updated_at":"2026-02-26T21:37:50Z","waiters":"","wisp_type":"","work_type":""}
